# Search, Filter, and Print Standards

- For any future screen that includes listing data, implement search and filtering in the same interaction style used in the address book:
  - Global search input remains visible.
  - Column-level filter inputs are toggled by a small search icon in the table header.
  - Sorting controls are attached to the relevant column headers, not in a disconnected control area.
- Keep filter and search behavior predictable:
  - Global search narrows all visible rows.
  - Column filters refine further (logical AND with global search).
  - Sorting applies to the already filtered result set.
- Reuse or extend existing helper patterns/functions for search/filter logic instead of introducing one-off implementations in each page.
- For future print features, always use the same site print standard:
  - Use `printWithSiteStandard(...)` (which routes through the official A4 print template).
  - Do not create ad-hoc print windows with inconsistent styling unless explicitly requested.
  - Keep report title, metadata, and table formatting aligned with current official print reports.
- When asked to review or refactor an existing page, preserve this unified behavior for search/filter and print unless the user requests a different UX.
